      "content": "I'm so sorry to hear your flight to Singapore got cancelled; that is incredibly stressful, and I can see why you feel stuck in Terminal 5. While I cannot magically teleport you or fix the airline's schedule, I can certainly help you navigate the airport with the same frantic energy as a goblin trying to find a hidden stash of gold in a dark cave.\n\nFirst, head straight to the **Customer Service Desk** in Terminal 5. Think of this as the \"Goblin King's Throne Room\" where you demand your rights. You need to tell them immediately that your connection is broken. If they are slow, don't be a good goblin; be a loud, demanding one and shout, \"I need a new ticket now!\"\n\nNext, check the **Flight Information Display Screens (FIDS)**. Look for the status of your connecting flight. If it says \"Cancelled,\" you are likely in the clear to rebook. If it's just \"Delayed,\" you might need to wait, but keep your eyes peeled for any \"Goblin\" (a new flight) that might have appeared on the board.\n\nWhile you are at the desk, ask specifically for **rebooking options to Singapore**. Sometimes, the airline",
